tip.text: Relaxing beach resort with decent amenities. Nice for a weekend holiday.
Wedges with nachos cheese - this dish requires no introduction. Not too much nor too little sauce.
Food was decent. And they serve complimentary iced water. Biggest problem was that there's too much mosquitos there in the evening. Bring your own insect repellent or mosquito coils.
Not like a fast food restaurant. It's a proper sit down resraurant with a polite lady serving. Doesn't speak English/Chinese but still able to order properly.
Clothes here at very affordable prices from 5000. Shop owners are friendly too. Fixed price shop so don't try to ask for a discount.
Fried chicken is tasty but please come with at least 2 other friends. One bowl of chicken (pic) is sufficient for 3. Different beers available. Affordable fast food!
Beautiful UNESCO heritage site to visit on Jeju Island. The peak is 180 meters high and you'll need about one hour at this place (hike up and down).
The Oreo Mille Crepe cake is just average. I had the iced honey lemon which was okay.
Sate chicken and chicken skin in peanut fondue was tasty, but a tad too sweet. Add a bowl of rice to go along.
Staffs barely speak English but menu isn't hard to understand with partial English words.
Nice list of little dishes you can choose from. If you love something, you can order it twice. Great value as well. Would say it's one of the best breakfast places in Copenhagen.
Tasty cod fish n chips. Didn't try the beef burger but overheard it's good, just a little lesser lettuce now. Get the dessert of the day - I had the brownies.
Careful when you stick yourself onto the wall for photos. Sometimes paint/ink isn't dry yet.
The mussels are to die for. Each bowl is just sufficient for 2 persons since they're so tasty and flavourful. Get a main course and end your meal with a chocolate ice cream and/or green tea.
Had the herring (3 flavours) and they're very challenging on my tongue (But tasty and fresh).
Waffles are tasty but the ice cream feels little stingy on the tip of the tongue. The scoop of ice cream was generous though!
Must try: fish skin (hkd 15), signature fish balls+ wanton noodles.
Didn't expect the pork ribs to be like pork chop. The skin was soft and tasty but the meat was too rough and hard.
There's always promos for Citibank/Standard chartered credit cards! Bring one there.

tip.text: Wonderful traditional desserts with buffet dinner. The traditional desserts are not in the menu.
Beer is excellent here. If you're here for the pork knuckle or schnitzel, it's much overrated.
Go for either the snapper, salmon or the seafood (snapper, scallops and prawn) meal. Japanese green tea is free flow.
